OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1779879767
OL,3,CAmber warning issued as London
OL,4,Ctemperatures rival Caribbean hotspots
OL,6,FTemperatures are forecast to reach 33C
OL,7,Fin southern England and the Midlands
OL,8,Fon Monday - higher than the UK's
OL,9,Fcurrent May temperature record of
OL,10,F32.8C.
OL,12,FHighs of 28C are expected in parts of
OL,13,Fsouth-east England on Friday before
OL,14,Fclimbing above 30C across swathes of
OL,15,FEngland and Wales over the following
OL,16,Fdays.
OL,18,FIt means many areas will also be
OL,19,Fhotter than top European holiday spots
OL,20,Fincluding Mykonos, Marbella and
OL,21,FBenidorm.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1779879767
OL,3,CAmber warning issued as London
OL,4,Ctemperatures rival Caribbean hotspots
OL,6,FVulnerable people may need extra
OL,7,Fsupport, with hotter indoor
OL,8,Ftemperatures also expected, according
OL,9,Fto the UKHSA.
OL,11,FMet Office deputy chief forecaster,
OL,12,FSteve Kocher, said: "It is likely that
OL,13,Fthe May and spring UK temperature
OL,14,Frecords will be broken over the bank
OL,15,Fholiday weekend, with forecast
OL,16,Ftemperatures surpassing the existing
OL,17,Frecord of 32.8C."
OL,26,@tD@UOUyD@QO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/9
