PN,40406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1779879767
OL,3,CAmber warning issued as London
OL,4,Ctemperatures rival Caribbean hotspots
OL,6,FCancer Research UK urge people to
OL,7,Fenjoy the sun safely by covering up
OL,8,Fand using sunscreen.
OL,10,FIts most recent data for the year 2022
OL,11,Fshows there were 20,980 new cases of
OL,12,Fmelanoma, the highest number it has
OL,13,Fever seen.
OL,15,FNew analysis from the charity also
OL,16,Fsuggests the number of people told
OL,17,Fthey have melanoma will reach 26,500 a
OL,18,Fyear by 2040.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1779879767
OL,3,CAmber warning issued as London
OL,4,Ctemperatures rival Caribbean hotspots
OL,6,FAccording to the NHS, the most
OL,7,Fvulnerable groups are older people,
OL,8,Fespecially women over the age of 75,
OL,9,For those who live alone or in a care
OL,10,Fhome.
OL,12,FPeople with long-term illnesses such
OL,13,Fas heart or lung conditions, diabetes,
OL,14,FParkinson's and some mental health
OL,15,Fconditions are at a higher risk, as
OL,16,Fwell as patients on multiple medicines.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1779879767
OL,3,CAmber warning issued as London
OL,4,Ctemperatures rival Caribbean hotspots
OL,6,FBabies and very young children will
OL,7,Falso find it hard to keep cool, along
OL,8,Fwith people dependent on alcohol or
OL,9,Fdrugs or people with Alzheimer's
OL,10,Fdisease.
OL,12,FWhat are the main risks?
OL,14,FNot drinking enough water, which can
OL,15,Fcause dehydration, while overheating
OL,16,Fcan make symptoms worse for people
OL,17,Fwith heart or breathing problems.
OL,19,FHeat exhaustion can happen when the
OL,20,Fbody overheats and loses too much
OL,21,Fwater and salt.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1779879767
OL,3,CAmber warning issued as London
OL,4,Ctemperatures rival Caribbean hotspots
OL,6,FSigns include tiredness, dizziness,
OL,7,Fheadaches, feeling sick, excessive
OL,8,Fsweating and being very thirsty.
OL,10,FIf people do not cool down within 30
OL,11,Fminutes, heat exhaustion can lead to
OL,12,Fheatstroke, a life-threatening illness.
OL,14,FIf you suspect someone has heat
OL,15,Fexhaustion, the NHS advises to move
OL,16,Fthem to a cool place, remove all
OL,17,Funnecessary clothing, giving them cool
OL,18,Fwater or a sports drink, and cooling
OL,19,Ftheir skin by spraying cool water or
OL,20,Ffanning them.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/9
